>
  <p>
    Ask three companies to "pump the tank" and you might get three slightly different jobs. The words
    pumping and cleaning are used loosely in the industry, and the gap between them isn't just
    semantics — it's the difference between a tank that's genuinely empty and one that's merely
    lighter. Knowing the distinction lets you compare quotes fairly and make sure the service actually
    protects your system.
  </p>

